name: ExtensionRatioRange
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.RatioRange` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `RatioRange` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `RatioRange` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`RatioRange` 0..* `RatioRange`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `RatioRange` 0..* `RatioRange`

Following are the generation technical comments:
FHIR R5 ComplexType `RatioRange` is representable via FHIR R4 extensions.
Element `RatioRange` is not mapped to FHIR R4, since FHIR R5 `RatioRange` is not mapped.

element.definition: A range of ratios expressed as a low and high numerator and a denominator.
element.comment: The stated low and high value are assumed to have arbitrarily high precision when it comes to determining which values are in the range. I.e. 1.99 is not in the range 2 -> 3.
